docs/ is the project's design-and-status record: architecture rationale (DECISIONS.md), a deferred lint-rule spec (DYLINT_RULES.md), and open-task tracking (STATUS.md). Nothing here is executable; it's the layer other docs and `.context/intent.md` point to for *why* and *what's pending*, not *what the code currently does*.

The three files are independent logs with no shared format, but they cross-reference: STATUS.md's open items and DYLINT_RULES.md's planned rules should trace back to ADRs in DECISIONS.md when they touch architecture, and DECISIONS.md is the terminology authority — retired terms banned elsewhere (`ctx-access`, `init-task`, `end-task`, `served_nodes`) are only legitimate inside DECISIONS.md itself and `docs/retired/**`. A key fact spanning the subtree: `docs/SPEC.md` is retired and moved to `docs/retired/SPEC.md` (ADR-052); no file here should be edited as if SPEC.md is still current, and its former content is now scattered across `.context/intent.md`, `Cargo.toml`/`clippy.toml`, the summarizer prompts, and DECISIONS.md.

DECISIONS.md is append-only — new architectural decisions go there as a new numbered ADR, never a rewrite of an old one. DYLINT_RULES.md describes nine unimplemented rules, two of which (1 and 4) have partial mechanical equivalents already enforced via scripts/ (`rationale_check.py`, `cycle_check.sh`); changes to those scripts should be checked against this file for drift. STATUS.md is the only file meant to change frequently and casually (task list, bump date on edits).

intent.md is absent for this directory, so no divergence check applies.